  22. ‌let insert_move src dst next =
  23.   if src.loc = dst.loc
  24.   then next
  25.   else instr_cons (Iop Imove) [|src|] [|dst|] next

  27. ‌let insert_moves src dst next =
  28.   let rec insmoves i =
  29.     if i >= Array.length src
  30.     then next
  31.     else insert_move src.(i) dst.(i) (insmoves (i+1))
  32.   in insmoves 0

  36. ‌val mutable redo_regalloc = false

  38. method makereg r =
  39.   match r.loc with
  40.     Unknown -> fatal_error "Reload.makereg"
  41.   | Reg _ -> r
  42.   | Stack _ ->
  43.       redo_regalloc <- true;
  44.       let newr = Reg.clone r in
  45.       (* Strongly discourage spilling this register *)
  46.       newr.spill_cost <- 100000;
  47.       newr

  49. method makeregs rv =
  50.   let n = Array.length rv in
  51.   let newv = Array.make n Reg.dummy in
  52.   for i = 0 to n-1 do newv.(i) <- self#makereg rv.(i) done;
  53.   newv

  55. method private makereg1 rv =
  56.   let newv = Array.copy rv in
  57.   newv.(0) <- self#makereg rv.(0);
  58.   newv

  60. method reload_operation op arg res =
  61.   (* By default, assume that arguments and results must reside
  62.      in hardware registers. For moves, allow one arg or one
  63.      res to be stack-allocated, but do something for
  64.      stack-to-stack moves *)
  65.   match op with
  66.     Imove | Ireload | Ispill ->
  67.       begin match arg.(0), res.(0) with
  68.         {loc = Stack s1}, {loc = Stack s2} when s1 <> s2 ->
  69.           ([| self#makereg arg.(0) |], res)
  70.       | _ ->
  71.           (arg, res)
  72.       end
  73.   | Iopaque ->
  74.       (* arg = result, can be on stack or register *)
  75.       assert (arg.(0).stamp = res.(0).stamp);
  76.       (arg, res)
  77.   | _ ->
  78.       (self#makeregs arg, self#makeregs res)

  80. method reload_test _tst args =
  81.   self#makeregs args

  83. method private reload i =
  84.   match i.desc with
  85.     (* For function calls, returns, etc: the arguments and results are
  86.        already at the correct position (e.g. on stack for some arguments).
  87.        However, something needs to be done for the function pointer in
  88.        indirect calls. *)
  89.     Iend | Ireturn | Iop(Itailcall_imm _) | Iraise _ -> i
  90.   | Iop(Itailcall_ind) ->
  91.       let newarg = self#makereg1 i.arg in
  92.       insert_moves i.arg newarg
  93.         {i with arg = newarg}
  94.   | Iop(Icall_imm _ | Iextcall _) ->
  95.       {i with next = self#reload i.next}
  96.   | Iop(Icall_ind) ->
  97.       let newarg = self#makereg1 i.arg in
  98.       insert_moves i.arg newarg
  99.         {i with arg = newarg; next = self#reload i.next}
  100.   | Iop op ->
  101.       let (newarg, newres) = self#reload_operation op i.arg i.res in
  102.       insert_moves i.arg newarg
  103.         {i with arg = newarg; res = newres; next =
  104.           (insert_moves newres i.res
  105.             (self#reload i.next))}
  106.   | Iifthenelse(tst, ifso, ifnot) ->
  107.       let newarg = self#reload_test tst i.arg in
  108.       insert_moves i.arg newarg
  109.         (instr_cons
  110.           (Iifthenelse(tst, self#reload ifso, self#reload ifnot)) newarg [||]
  111.           (self#reload i.next))
  112.   | Iswitch(index, cases) ->
  113.       let newarg = self#makeregs i.arg in
  114.       insert_moves i.arg newarg
  115.         (instr_cons (Iswitch(index, Array.map (self#reload) cases)) newarg [||]
  116.           (self#reload i.next))
  117.   | Icatch(rec_flag, handlers, body) ->
  118.       let new_handlers = List.map
  119.           (fun (nfail, handler) -> nfail, self#reload handler)
  120.           handlers in
  121.       instr_cons
  122.         (Icatch(rec_flag, new_handlers, self#reload body)) [||] [||]
  123.         (self#reload i.next)
  124.   | Iexit i ->
  125.       instr_cons (Iexit i) [||] [||] dummy_instr
  126.   | Itrywith(body, handler) ->
  127.       instr_cons (Itrywith(self#reload body, self#reload handler)) [||] [||]
  128.         (self#reload i.next)

  130. method fundecl f num_stack_slots =
  131.   redo_regalloc <- false;
  132.   let new_body = self#reload f.fun_body in
  133.   ({fun_name = f.fun_name; fun_args = f.fun_args;
  134.     fun_body = new_body; fun_codegen_options = f.fun_codegen_options;
  135.     fun_dbg  = f.fun_dbg;
  136.     fun_poll = f.fun_poll;
  137.     fun_contains_calls = f.fun_contains_calls;
  138.     fun_num_stack_slots = Array.copy num_stack_slots;
  139.    },
  140.    redo_regalloc)
  141. end
